				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Only problem is unlike chanters we don't get AA's that extend our charms and all.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Charms cannot be extended.  Total Domination makes charms more stable (how no one has a clue).  Runes do almost nothing when charming (I can get an AA in a little over 30 minutes solo in CoD) because a hasted mob = no rune in 1-2 rounds.  There are reasons why charming for Mages is more difficult to exp on than charming for Necro/Dru/Enchanter.
<br />

<br />
1.  You Charm in BoT, where 85% of the mobs summon.  Where I kill in CoD, I don't get summoned.  Where most Enchanters kill in HoH, there are very very few summoners (named in basements?).
<br />

<br />
2.  Your charmed pets have crap for damage output.  I know Enchanter charmed pets in HoH (I've duoed with a few) can quad for 544+.  My charmed pet in CoD can quad for 589 (can also get a Necro pet if I want).  Druids I'm sketchy on.
<br />

<br />
3.  The charmable mobs are balanced extremely well against the mobs you would prefer to exp on in BoT.  They hit less, have less hit points.  The Militis/Kriger/<insertname> types have very high hitpoints.  Mobs in CoD die to my hasted charm pet in 10-20 seconds (really).  They die so fast it's best to just FD the pet, let it regen and then recharm adn pull 3 mob mobs for it to tank at once and kill.
<br />

<br />
4.  You shouldn't have the spell.  Honestly, the addition of these spells to the Magicians spellbook was really cool, but all it does is raise issues when people die over and over again and then look at another class that has been charming from at least level 20 and whine about how unbalanced it is.  Magicians have 1 charm/mezz spell, and it comes with GREAT risk.
<br />

<br />
So you die over and over using an ability your class wasn't designed to use (note key phrase in there).  It does not come as a surprise.  On a better note, most people (it doesn't matter what class) will die to a summoner on a charm break.  Necros always have a better chance because of Channeling Focus and Feign Death.  We also focus more on our HPs than other casters since HP = mana for us.
<br />

<br />
The reason why I mention the Necro pet is because they cast some good damage spells and will usually try to cast on me instead of rushing me on a charm break.  Making it that much simpler.<br />_________________<br />Lich Zebulak Thule
<br />
Arch Lich of Cazic-Thule
<br />
Veeshan
<br />

<br />
"You won't believe this.  I'm an American Indian, but they call me Whiteman."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
